FRONTLINE ROADS v0.32.3 PERSISTENCE AND SURVEY RELIABILITY AUDIT

Release: 0.32.3-persistence-survey-reliability
Scope: facility persistence, non-destructive save restoration, destroyed-gate presentation, survey-road acquisition reliability

Confirmed causes corrected:
- Same-schema saves lacking runtime.combatInitialized could be treated as new combat and lose the complete defense collection during normalization.
- Construction, repair, upgrade and gate-conversion actions could be lost when the page was refreshed before the periodic autosave.
- Survey facilities depended on cross-origin POST only, so one blocked transport mode could place every survey facility into an error state.
- Initial and restored road graphs did not always reconstruct loaded/integrated road-chunk coverage.
- Destroyed gates used a generic ruin marker and did not clearly communicate that enemies could pass.

Implemented behavior:
- Existing combat is inferred from an established city and home base; defense data is normalized in place and never cleared by a missing runtime flag.
- Zero-HP facilities remain persisted as ruins, including gates and survey facilities.
- Successful construction, repair, upgrade and gate conversion save immediately.
- Defense destruction and city defeat queue a critical save after the active simulation step; pagehide performs a final local save.
- Road-chunk coverage is reconstructed from graph coordinates and merged into loaded/integrated state.
- Overpass acquisition uses form-encoded POST with a safe GET fallback and remembers the successful transport per endpoint. JSONP remains absent.
- Survey failures enter RETRY_WAIT with a diagnostic and 90-second retry cooldown; success clears the error state.
- Destroyed gates render as an open breach with OPEN and report 破壊済み・敵通行可.

